Quote:  <i>ko[o]kopu</i>, a fresh-water fish (Galaxias fasciatius), a fat, sluggish fish, formerly common in open drains and caught by children with cupped hands; name corrupted by them to cock-a-bully and abbreviated <i>bully</i>.
Notes:  Andersen Maori Words in English

