Date:  0/0/1967
Source:  Animals of NZ, The
Author:  NATUSCH
Vol / Page:  229
Edition:
Quote:   Family BLENNiiDAE (cockabullies). is `cockabully' a transliteration and transference of `kokopu', the Maori word for a different fish, the galaxiid; or does `kokopu' come from `cockabully'? in any case, cockabully, kokopu and bully are used for quite different fishes.
